project  and  the  reason  why  they  do  that,  it  is  because  they  recog-
nize  that  there  is  an  economic  cost  to  that  disruption  that  has  to
go into that equation when they determine what is the best course
of  action  for  the  public.  So  that  is  what  I  would  say  in  terms  of
workforce,  to  ensure  that  we  are  training  researchers  and  opening
our aperture, if you will, to embrace folks from multiple disciplines
and  not  just  the  civil  engineering  community  anymore,  not  that
they are not important and critical to this but it needs to go beyond
that.

Chairman WU. Mr. Iwasaki.
